A Salute to Noun O'Clock Live (my /firstdraft )

Tonight is the 1,000th *straight* & final show. Many won't know Noun O'Clock Live, but if you've come across @zerorightsmedia w/ @toadyhawk.eth & @jackwyldes.eth that was born out of Noun O'Clock LIve--a daily show for all things /nouns 

I was there in the beginning as a daily listener. NOC Live helped me make Nouns my first home in web3. They were fun & informative, dedicated to helping people like me learn how a DAO could steward 10s of millions of dollars to promote a brand & do good in the world. 

On 8/8/22, they did a 24 hr show for the 1st Anniversary of Nouns. I was one of their guests because I had just joined Nouncil (Nounish Council) & had won my first prophouse. That show regularly comes into my mind. I have art on my wall from it (s/o @messhup ). I can't tell my web3 story w/o talking a lot about The NounSquare & NOC Live. 

So, thank you @toadyhawk.eth @benbodhi @nounishprof  @supertightwoody @robotfishgirl @aubtoshi among others ü´°

Very misleading to be a FIP. The Farcaster protocol as laid out in its specification is NOT recieving a direct message system with this update. 

The Warpcast Direct messaging system will be further opened beyond existing APIs

To me that‚Äôs great for programmability but NOT a protocol feature! 

A feature built on top of the protocol sure but not protocol level

Though as Frames also are a client level, non protocol feature I get why it may be an FIP

Though I already see posts from people saying DCs will be at protocol level because of the FIP label.

TLDR: very very excited about DCs opening up, though as always I prefer more precise language üòÇ

Why DCs matter? Darn it just look at telegram bot markets, they are HUGE! Great for devs, great for AI/programmable workflows!

The Unwritten Rules of Farcaster (a thread 1/11)


1.	Don‚Äôt ask for follows‚Äîmost users ignore or avoid those who do.
2.	Engagement matters‚Äîtreat it as a social network, not just a broadcasting platform.
3.	The algorithm prioritizes engagement‚Äîinteract with content you like to train your feed.
4.	Give likes freely to support content you enjoy.
5.	Reply thoughtfully‚Äîgeneric responses don‚Äôt add value and may be ignored.
6.	Tag people with purpose‚Äîavoid tagging non-followers without a good reason.
7.	Use channels to connect‚Äîthey‚Äôre a safe space for engaging beyond your followers.
8.	If you‚Äôre being ignored, check your spam label‚Äîmany won‚Äôt see your replies if you‚Äôre at Level 0 or 1.
9.	Rules are looser with friends‚Äîbanter freely, but remember relationships take time to build.
10.	Farcaster is a unique, close-knit community‚Äîengage authentically, be patient, and you‚Äôll find your place.
